column5: Gave another try to the whities today. Glad I did as it was best day so far this season.  From 7:30 till 10am final score was 12/15....Meegs knocked them down again. Maybe at the very end of the not so great ice season we'll get few hot bite days.  Several shots for your viewing pleasure. Was so cold. The two that made it on the ice froze within 2 min. Had to release them inside the hole very quickly to help them get back to the deep.                   Cheers, Ice Fisherman
Awesome whities.  I miss those big bulldoggin whities
Very nice Emil. x2  Why am i not surprised  Often imitated  Never duplicated  Good shootin ice  Sweet picks too  Paul
Nice day! Not many to be had like that this year
nice nice be out for sunday maybe see you out there be fishn kemp

Good for you Emil.  Some great shots there too  Enjoy your dinner!!!
Gunna give it a honest effort this weekend Heading out Saturday and Sunday to attempt the allusive (for me!!) Simcoe white fish!  Or at least to see Jer hoist a big one.  Those are great pics Emil!
